clue: "Of neither Darcy nor Wickham could she think, without feeling that she had been blind, partial, prejudiced, absurd"

response: Austen

clue: "Why didn't you tell me that that infernal harpooneer was a cannibal?"

response: Melville

clue: "Remedios the beauty stayed there wandering through the desert of solitude... maturing in her dreams without nightmares"

response: Gabriel García Márquez

clue: "The men upon the floor were going about their work. Neither squeals of hogs nor tears of visitors made any difference to them"

response: Upton Sinclair

clue: "In the actions of all men... where there is no impartial arbiter, one must consider the final result"

response: Machiavelli

